  "text": "As shown in Figure 2 , after 120 days, the catalase activities were decreased except sterilized soil samples, which indicate that the petroleum hydrocarbon inhibited the catalase activity, that is the toxic action during petroleum hydrocarbon degradation led to decrease the catalase activity. There was no significant difference between the soil samples incubated with aboriginal microorganisms and bacteria. The amount of microorganism was showed without significant influence on catalase activity. The catalase activity was increased in the phytoremediation areas [CITATION_1] .",
